<subSubSection id="C33B07F8072DA23453D2EEE7FA584E5D" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="292" pageId="6" pageNumber="291" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9E5473072DA23453D2EEE7FA584E5D" blockId="6.[136,1452,1954,2089]" lastBlockId="7.[136,1452,158,365]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="292" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B9558861072DA23553D2EEE7FFEA488C" bold="true" box="[136,203,1955,1981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB02982072DA2355383EEE7FE40488C" author="Nees Von Esenbeck, C. G." box="[217,353,1955,1981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="291" pagination="91 - 93" refId="ref3929" refString="Nees Von Esenbeck, C. G. (1832) Acanthaceae Indiae Orientalis. In: N. Wallich (Ed.) Plantae Asiaticae rariores, or, Descriptions and figures of a select number of unpublished East Indian plants, 3. Treuttel et Wurtz, London, pp. 91 - 93." type="book chapter" year="1832">Nees (1832)</bibRefCitation>
described the species based on 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA072DA23551E4EEE6FC72488C" box="[702,851,1954,1981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="291" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">three syntype</specimenCount>
gatherings distributed by Wallich (“Wall. Cat. n. 2509 h [‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF0072DA23553EAEE82FE9E48D1" authority="? Herb." authorityName="Herb." box="[176,447,1990,2017]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis id="B9558861072DA23553EAEE82FE4D48D1" box="[176,364,1990,2016]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">Barleria cristata</emphasis>
? Herb.
</taxonomicName>
Wight’], and i [‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF0072DA2355121EE82FCC548D0" authority="? Herb. Heyn." authorityName="Herb. Heyn." box="[635,996,1990,2017]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pungens">
<emphasis id="B9558861072DA2355121EE82FC1F48D1" box="[635,830,1990,2016]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">Barleria pungens</emphasis>
? Herb. Heyn.
</taxonomicName>
’]”) and Wight (“Herb. propr. n. 14”), but did not specify one of these as the type. The specimen number 14 distributed by Wight, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB02982072DA23557A0EEAEFFD34718" author="Wight, R. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W." pageId="6" pageNumber="291" refId="ref4561" refString="Wight, R. &amp; Arnott, G. A. W. (1934) Prodromus florae peninsula Indiae orientalis. Parbury, Allen, &amp; Co., London, pp. 4." type="book" year="1934">Wight &amp; Arnott (1934: 4)</bibRefCitation>
, was actually a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF0072DA2355140E14AFDBF4719" box="[538,670,2062,2088]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Ranunculus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9558861072DA2355140E14AFDBF4719" box="[538,670,2062,2088]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">Ranunculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, prompting 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB02982072DA2355072E14BFCCA4718" author="Nees Von Esenbeck, C. G." box="[808,1003,2063,2089]" pageId="6" pageNumber="291" pagination="46 - 519" refId="ref3986" refString="Nees Von Esenbeck, C. G. (1847) Acanthaceae. In: de Candolle, A. L. P. P. (Ed.) Prodromus Systematis Naturalis Regni Vegetabilis 11. Masson, Paris, pp. 46 - 519." type="journal article" year="1847">Nees (1847: 224)</bibRefCitation>
to later indicate this as “Wight h. propr. n. 1955”. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB02982072CA23453A3E9DAFD7F4F88" author="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R." box="[249,606,158,185]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" pagination="81 - 130" refId="ref4246" refString="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R. (2010) Revision of the genus Barleria (Acanthaceae) in India. Rheedea 20: 81 - 130." type="journal article" year="2010">Shendage &amp; Yadav (2010: 105)</bibRefCitation>
designated a specimen indicated as ‘Herb. Prop., 
<emphasis id="B9558861072CA23457C2E9DAFA284F89" box="[1176,1289,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">Wight s.n.</emphasis>
’ from Madras Herbarium (MH) as 
<typeStatus id="549AEAD1072CA2345235E986FEF84FED" box="[367,473,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">lectotype</typeStatus>
. Although this specimen was collected by Wight, there is no indication that it bears the number 14 or 1955. So, it cannot be considered original material of Nees, and hence their attempted lectotypification cannot be followed. We could find 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA072CA2345153E84EFD9E4E15" box="[521,703,266,292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
, one at GZU (GZU000249420) from Nees Herbarium that bears the label 
<emphasis id="B9558861072CA234539CE86BFFEE4E78" box="[198,207,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">‘</emphasis>
2509/h 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF0072CA234527FE86BFD0F4E79" authority="? Hb. Wight." authorityName="Hb. Wight." box="[293,558,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis id="B9558861072CA234527FE86BFEBA4E79" box="[293,411,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">B. cristata</emphasis>
? Hb. Wight.
</taxonomicName>
’ and 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA072CA2345130E86BFC314E79" box="[618,784,302,329]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
on a single sheet at K, K001116287 and K001116288 with label 2509h and 
<date id="FF9F72B3072CA2345218E816FEA54E5C" box="[322,388,338,365]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" value="2509-01">2509i</date>
, respectively. Here, we choose one of the specimens from K (K001116287) as a 
<typeStatus id="549AEAD1072CA2345651E816FA544E5D" box="[1291,1397,338,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
